      " {\n",
      "  \"transcriptcomponenttypename\":\"Answer\",\n",
      "  \"transcriptpersonname\":null,\n",
      "  \"companyofperson\":null,\n",
      "  \"speakertypename\":null,\n",
      "  \"componenttext\":\"Bruce Hamilton, Morgan Stanley. I mean, obviously, the earnings growth was a very good number in the period of up 8%. And I guess the didn't move. Given that, to achieve sort of 3.8% sort of return to shareholders, which more of 5% if I x out the FX monies. On the plate, it doesn't look that impressive. I guess looking forward, realizations will improve, but should we also the the earnings growth will moderate. I mean, what would you expect as a more quite normal level of earnings growth? Or is sort of 15% per year something you think is achievable?\"\n",
